\f0\fs36 \cf0 Introduction
\fs24 \
TeXGyreHerosTXfonts is a combination of TeXGyreHeros for the Latin letters and the math font from the LaTeX txfonts package for the greek letters.  \
\

\fs36 Rationale Behind Selecting These Fonts
\fs24 \
I am a fan of Helvetica for its clean lines and its relatively heavy line weight. Since Helvetica is not free, I have chosen the free Helvetica clone, TeXGyreHeros.  Originally, I tried the Helvetica Clone, NimbusSansL, but it did not have diacritic characters (i.e. the "bars" and "hats" that are commonly used in math mode).\
  \
I chose the txfonts package for several reasons.  The txfonts package is a popular LaTeX font package with full math support, and it has recently been enhanced as the newtx package.  The line weight of the greek letters in the txfonts (newtx) package is comparable to TeXGyreHeros, and their shapes appeal to me.  The txfonts (newtx) package also has TeXGyreHeros as its sans-serif font.  Thus, one can easily load the txfonts (newtx) package into LaTeX and typeset equations that look nearly identical to equations created using matplotlib's mathtext and the TeXGyreHerosTXfonts.ttf font.\
\

